oss-country day for eventers in Versailles.\", \"from\": 4700, \"to\": 4793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4782, \"end\": 4792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 0.999991761120161, \"rank\": 8.238947662641371e-06, \"text\": \"Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The equine stars of the Games and their riders will compete on a 5km cross-country course over artificial and natural obstacles in the erstwhile hunting grounds of former French kings.\", \"from\": 4795, \"to\": 4979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4966, \"end\": 4972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999908881519733, \"rank\": 8.248534408322488e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have managed to avoid postponing the event due to the rain over the past two days but Sunday's weather is expected to favour horses that are used to softer, wet ground more than those coming from drier regions.\", \"from\": 4981, \"to\": 5202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain, Germany and France are among the favourites.\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5204, \"end\": 5211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9992855562750227, \"rank\": 0.0007149545165440365, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 5213, \"end\": 5220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8129837098202275, \"rank\": 0.23003694013157774, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpe